-- Total’s European Refining Margin Drops 21% in First Quarter
-- B y   T a r a   P a t e l
-- 2013-04-15T10:33:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-15/total-s-european-refining-margin-drops-21-in-first-quarter.html
Total SA (FP) , Europe’s biggest refiner,
reported a 21 percent drop in first-quarter European refining
margins compared with the final three months of 2012.  The European indicator fell to $26.90 a ton from $33.90 a
ton in the previous quarter, according to data published on the
Paris-based oil explorer’s  website .  The average selling price for liquids was $106.70 a barrel
while the average price for gas was $7.31 million British
Thermal Units.  Refining margins are the profit from turning a barrel of
oil into fuel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tara Patel in Paris at 
